            <h3 class="detail-title">What is image resizing?</h3>
            <aside>
                Resizing is the process of changing the size of an image without cutting anything out. When you resize
                an image, you're just changing the file size. Because size does matter on occasion.
            </aside>
            <aside>
                Resizing your photo might make it fit into a specific area on a screen, such as a blog or social network
                post. Smaller photographs weigh less than larger ones, which might help speed up the uploading process
                or free up storage space on your devices.
            </aside>
        </div>
    </div>
